** Modules and Packages**
--> help organize Python code and reuse functionality without rewriting it
1) MODULE :- It is a Python file(.py) containing functions, variables, or classes.
Example: math, random, datetime
ex:- import math
     print(math.sqrt(16))  
     print(math.factorial(5)) 
2) Importing Specific Functions;
ex:- from math import factorial, ceil
     print(factorial(6))  
     print(ceil(4.3))    
3) Creating Your Own Module;
--> i) by creating a file mymodule.py :- 
def greet(name):
    return f"Hello, {name}!"
--> ii) using it in another file :- 
import mymodule
print(mymodule.greet("Shravya"))
4) PACKAGE :- It is a folder containing multiple modules and a special __init__.py file
--> It allows  to organize large projects
syntax:- myproject/
         __init__.py
         math_utils.py
         string_utils.py
Usage:- from myproject import math_utils, string_utils
5) Common Built-in Modules :-
=> os → interact with operating system
=> sys → system-specific parameters
=> random → generate random numbers
=> datetime → work with dates and times
=> math → math operations
ex:- import random
     print(random.randint(1, 100))  
